Class HttpLoadTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.LogVector
      • dfischer.utils.HttpLoadTest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LogVectorInterface

    public abstract class HttpLoadTest
extends LogVector
    Abstract basis class of all load test programs and all load test threads (simulated users).

    A real instance of this class must be created for every simulated user before the load test really starts.
    This class contains also an user specific log vector which is used to collect the test output of a single loop.
     
    This class contains also a static reference to the context of all simulated users.

    See Also:
    LogVector, getUserContextTable()

      Additional of searching the occurrence of a simple string, the following special search patterns are supported:
      • ![<search text>] means that the search text must not occur inside the received content.
      • #<int>[<search text>] means that the search text occurs exactly <int> times inside the received content.
      • #<int>-[<search text>] means that the search text occurs at minimum <int> times inside the received content.
      • #<int1>-<int2>[<search text>] means that the search text occurs at minimum <int1> times but not more than <int2> times inside the received content.

      #1-2[Order Number]The search text "Order Number" must occur at minimum one time and at maximum two times inside the received content
      #3-[new order]The search text "new order" must occur at minimum three times inside the received content

        Additional of searching the occurrence of a simple string, the following special search patterns are supported:
        • ![<search text>] means that the search text must not occur inside the received content.
        • #<int>[<search text>] means that the search text occurs exactly <int> times inside the received content.
        • #<int>-[<search text>] means that the search text occurs at minimum <int> times inside the received content.
        • #<int1>-<int2>[<search text>] means that the search text occurs at minimum <int1> times but not more than <int2> times inside the received content.
         
        Search String Examples:
        helloThe search text "hello" must occur at least one time inside the received content
        ![ORA-01652]The search text "ORA-01652" must not occur inside the received content
        #1[Dear Mr.]The search text "Dear Mr." must occur exactly one time inside the received content
        #1-2[Order Number]The search text "Order Number" must occur at minimum one time and at maximum two times inside the received content
        #3-[new order]The search text "new order" must occur at minimum three times inside the received content

        Parameters:
        testURL - reference to URL call
        threadStep - current execution step of thread
        recordedStatus - HTTP status code of originally recorded data
        recordedContentType - MIME type of originally recorded data
        searchString - search text, that must be part of the received content. A value of null effects, that any content is accepted.
        Returns:
        true, if the comparison of the HTTP status code, the MIME type and the search string was successful.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        See Also:
        HttpTestURL, LogVector, PerformanceData
